    intro: "Lin Huiyin was the first Chinese woman to study and professionally practice architecture. Together with her husband Liang Sicheng, she systematically documented historical Chinese architecture before wars and modernization could destroy it. At the same time, she was a celebrated poet and hosted literary salons in Peking that became the intellectual center of the Crescent Moon Society.",
